<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. The call uses strncmp(RefText, UTASSERT_PREFIX, sizeof(UTASSERT_PREFIX) - 1) with n = 9 ("UTASSERT_" length). There is no check that RefText is non-NULL or that the object RefText points to contains at least n bytes or a terminating '\0' within its bounds. If RefText points to a non-null-terminated or smaller buffer (for example: char small[4] = {'U','T','A','B'}; RefText = small;), or is NULL, strncmp may read beyond the bounds of the referenced object, causing an out-of-bounds access and undefined behaviour.
</scenario>
